    "causal_summary": "The spec-kit generators that produce `description.json` and `graph-metadata.json` over-reach and churn. The backfill CLI ignores its positional folder arg and defaults to the repo-wide root, runtime search regenerates a global cache as a side effect, the description path stamps wall-clock time and writes unconditionally, the status normalizer admits free-text prose with em-dashes, `mergeGraphMetadata` drops `parent_id` and `children_ids` on a re-derive, the `specFolder` path shape is inconsistent between the two generators, and the global `descriptions.json` regen pulls in other sessions' folders. The visible symptom is unscoped cross-session commit churn that buries real diffs, plus a latent lineage-loss risk on the merge path. No prior research has examined the generated-JSON quality and safety surface as a whole.",
